 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyphyr>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 698<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 6:48:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1692.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage Conj Focus Items - What do they really do?</span><hr size=1> Necklace = Reagent Conservation by another name : 15% chance of not using reagent (malachite, cats eye agate, pearl, etc) when casting a spell. Does not apply to enchant/imbue type spells.<br>
<br>
Bracer = Improved Damage by another name : Up to 20% extra damage on DDs/Bolts.<br>
<br>
Shoulder = Extended Enhancement by another name : 15% increase in buff duration<br>
<br>
Ring = Spell Casting Haste by another name : 15% reduction in cast time on spells with a cast time of 3.0 secs or greater (Complete Heal spells not effected)<br>
<br>
Earring = Mana Preservation (15%) on agressive spells.<br>
<br>
