<br>
For the permanent Foci :<br>
Level I effects spells up to level 20<br>
Level II effects spells up to level 44<br>
Level III effects spells up to level 60<br>
Level IV effects spells up to level 65<br>
<br>
For the summoned foci, the level breaks are:<br>
Rings : 29/51/60/65<br>
Mantles : 16/49/60/65<br>
Bracers : 34/52/60/65<br>
Earrings : 24/50/60/65<br>
Chokers : 12/44/60/65<br>
<br>
The numbers are the maximum level spell that the item in question will work on.<br>
<br>
Diviine - your example/question is rather confused. At some points you refer to the level 34 Earring, and at others you talk about the rings - in a seemingly interchangable manner. The earring is not spell haste (it is mana preservation), and as such you won't notice a change in cast time with or without it regardless of what else you are wearing.<br>
<br>
For the situation of the mask (spell haste 2) vs. the ring, however, it is a valid question. They provide identical effects, but they have different cutoffs on when they work. Assuming a mage summoning his own foci:<br>
<br>
For a character of level 33 or lower, there is no difference between the two, since you only have level 29 and lower spells and both items provide a 15% casting time reduction for them.<br>
<br>
For a character of level 34 to 38, the mask is better. Either would work on spells from 1-29, but only the mask will work on 34s.<br>
<br>
From 39-48, the ring is (technically) better, since a new ring which works on spells up to level 51 is aquired at 39. You can, however, skip the ring during these levels since the mask will still work at the same effect on every single spell you have.<br>
<br>
From 49+ the ring is absolutely better, since you now have spells that the level 39 ring will work on but the mask won't.  At this point, the only real benefit you gain from the mask's effect is a reduction in cast time to summon the ring itself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=diviine>Diviine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(1/2/03 6:28:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1692.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage Conj Focus Items - What do they really do?</span><hr size=1> Sorry for changing those around. 3am soes that to a mages brain <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
